article.headline: Lipscomb 59, Georgia St 57 (OT)
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Matt Jarboe hit a 3-pointer and Georgia State didn't score for more than four minutes in overtime as Lipscomb came from behind for a 59-57 victory on Saturday. Jarboe's 3-pointer gave the Bisons (8-3, 3-1 Atlantic Sun Conference) a 58-55 lead with 2:40 to play, but Georgia State (5-8, 2-3) couldn't score until Marcus Brown hit a jumper to make it 59-57 with 59 seconds remaining. After a defensive stop, Brown missed a shot to tie the game, but grabbed his own rebound and was fouled by Jarboe with 1 second left. Brown, who scored 18 points, missed both free-throw attempts to end the game. Brian Fisk, the Bisons' only double-digit scorer with 19 points, forced overtime after hitting a one-handed runner from 15 feet to tie the game at 55 with 0.4 seconds left. Georgia State led by six at halftime and as many as 10 in the second half. Sylvester Morgan scored 15 points and Boyd Copeland added 10 for the Panthers.
